if self.name: 
    ....

@rhyolight 
> So I can specify claBurnInPeriod=0 and get the previous behavior?

yes, but `None`, see doc for diff `0/None`

@tseaver Why not

```python
if self.view_query is not None:
     view = resource['view'] = {}
     view['query'] = self.view_query
else:
     # Schema can only be used on non-queries.
     resource['schema'] = {'fields': _build_schema_resource(self._schema)}
```

and then just drop out the `schema` from `resource` above. Seems a bit silly to add and `del` when we could do this and avoid instead.

The portability of using `push` with individual path components is nice, but it might be more valuable to extract the two "literal" paths used in this file into statics:
```
static CFLAGS_PATH: &'static str = "src/cffi/native_engine.cflags";
static C_PATH: &'static str = "src/cffi/native_engine.c";
```
...so it's more obvious that they're intended to correspond.
